  "texts": [
    "We note our setting assumes less exact information and is thus more realistic: Jiang et al.",
    "evaluate with perfect statement-level FL, whereas AutoSDuses perfect method-level FL and the bug report, and thus needs to also identify which statement is faulty within the method based on available information.",
    "When evaluating the generated patches, we run the tests provided by each dataset for each bug; a fix that makes all tests pass is deemed a plausible patch, and plausible patches are manually inspected to see if they are semantically equivalent with the developer patch.",
    "Semantically equivalent fixes are deemed correct; semantic equivalence is determined by going through the generated patches and finding counterexamples where the behavior of the developer patch and generated patch would diverge.",
    "This is important to ensure that the LLM is not simply making all tests pass and thus being potentially misleading, but actually correctly fixing the bug."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}